descript.purpose: Shows the current city council district boundaries.

idinfo.accconst: Requestor must contact Charlotte-Mecklenburg Planning Department to obtain latest data. The data should only be obtained by contacting the Charlotte-Mecklenburg Planning Department.
idinfo.useconst: This GIS data has been compiled from a variety of sources. Any data or other GIS related product or service may contain inaccuracies or errors from the original sources or from subsequent reproduction, derivation, or manipulation. Consequently, this information is to be used only as a guide. The Charlotte-Mecklenburg Planning Department assumes no liability and makes no warranties or representations whatsoever regarding the quality, content, completeness, suitability, adequacy, or currency of such information and data. Furthermore, the Charlotte-Mecklenburg Planning Department shall not be liable for any misuse or decisions which the user may make based on these data, including the reselling of the data in its present form.
idinfo.native: Microsoft Windows XP Version 5.1 (Build 2600) Service Pack 3; ESRI ArcCatalog 9.3.1.1850

attracc.attraccr: The accuracy is dependent on the Boar of Election voting precincts data

dataqual.logic: Layer was developed using voting precincts as building blocks. Some minor positional errors may exist.
dataqual.complete: Layer is complete with continual effort to correct errors as they are discovered.

procstep.procdesc: This layer is updated during redistricting process using the board of elections voting precinct file and the newly annexed areas.

altsys.altenc: Explicit elevation coordinate included with horizontal coordinates

attrdomv.udom: Sequential unique whole numbers that are automatically generated.

attr.attrdef: Email of City Council District Rep
Area of feature in internal units squared.

attrdomv.udom: Positive real numbers that are automatically generated.

distinfo.distliab: This is not a legal document and should not be used as such. Once this data is distributed, the Charlotte-Mecklenburg Planning Department is not liable for its use nor is it responsible for any misuse of the data.

stdorder.ordering: Call office during open hours to request a digital copy of the data. Can be provided on disk or FTP.
stdorder.turnarnd: dependent on request - FTP is immediate

metainfo.metstdn: FGDC Content Standards for Digital Geospatial Metadata
